TY  - JOUR
AU  - van Binsbergen, Jules H
AU  - Nozawa, Yoshio
AU  - Schwert, Michael
T1  - Duration-Based Valuation of Corporate Bonds
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhae054
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 38
IS  - 1
SP  - 158
EP  - 191
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We decompose corporate bond and equity index returns into duration-matched government bond returns and the excess returns over this duration-matched counterfactual, which we term duration-adjusted returns. Compared with previously used excess return definitions (ie, returns in excess of Treasury bills), our decomposition leads to markedly different return patterns and asset pricing implications. In particular, we find that investment-grade bonds earn a small credit risk premium, comparable in magnitude to the convenience yield, and that duration adjustment resolves the CAPM’s failure to price corporate bonds. These findings highlight the importance of adjusting for nonstationary interest rate environments in asset pricing tests.
Y2  - 2/8/2025
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhae054
ER  - 



