TY  - JOUR
AU  - Jansen, Kristy A E
T1  - Long-Term Investors, Demand Shifts, and Yields
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhae071
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 38
IS  - 1
SP  - 114
EP  - 157
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - I exploit a Dutch reform in the regulatory discount curve that makes the liabilities of pension funds and insurance companies (P&amp;Is) more sensitive to changes in 20-year interest rates but less so to longer maturity rates. Following the reform, P&amp;Is reduced their longest maturity bond holdings but increased those with 20-year maturities, steepening the long end of the yield curve. Using the reform as a shock to identify price elasticities of demand at the sector level based on holdings across maturity buckets and time, I show that banks are more price elastic than other investors and absorb demand shocks.
Y2  - 2/8/2025
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhae071
ER  - 



