TY  - JOUR
AU  - Chen, Wen
AU  - Wang, Yajun
T1  - Dynamic Market Making with Asymmetric Information and Market Power
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhae062
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 38
IS  - 1
SP  - 235
EP  - 293
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We study the dynamics of trading volume and bid-ask spread using a multiperiod trading model with oligopolistic market makers. Traders smooth out their trading even though they are not strategic, and thus trading persists after the arrival of information or liquidity shocks. Traders act quickly on their private information while postponing hedging trades until later periods. The market power of market makers enables them to widen bid-ask spreads when trading incentives are heightened. Consequently, both trading volume and bid-ask spread may exhibit U-shaped patterns. Our model calibration aligns with the empirical intraday patterns observed in bid-ask spreads and trading volumes. (JEL D53, D61, D82, G12, G14, G18)
Y2  - 2/8/2025
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhae062
ER  - 



